<http://www.spektrix.com/chemainustheatrefestivalsociety/event/19406ARPCTRTMJJNQRQTDHGGDRQSJQJBH>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Godspell";
  schema:description """
	FEB 20 - MAR 29<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Conceived and Originally Directed by JOHN-MICHAEL TEBELAK<span><br/></span>MUSIC AND NEW LYRICS BY STEPHEN SCHWARTZ<span><br/></span>Originally Produced on the New York Stage by EDGAR LANSBURY / STUART DUNCAN / JOSEPH BERUH<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Prepare ye for Godspell, the classic folk-rock hit from Wicked's composer, Stephen Schwartz! This celebration and exploration of creating community and sacrificial love explodes with catchy music, a talented cast of actor-instrumentalists and playful parables in vibrant, contemporary, and fresh theatrical magic.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Content Advisory:  Depictions of crucifixion and biblical references. Recommended for ages 8+<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Run Time: 2 hours (including intermission)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Join us for lunch or dinner in the Playbill Dining Room! Dining can be added to your order after selecting your theatre tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h1><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://purchase.chemainustheatrefestival.ca/TicketSubscriptions\"> Subscriptions Available - ORDER NOW</a></h1><span><br/></span>
""";
